        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 27 at 3:01PM MDT by NWS Denver CO</headline>
        <description>At 301 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Firestone, or 20 miles south of Greeley, moving southeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Brighton, Firestone, Frederick, Fort Lupton, Lochbuie, Hudson and
Wattenburg.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
